         <listPerson>
            <person sex="1">
              
                  
                  <persName xml:lang="gez" xml:id="n1" type="birth">ሮስ፡ ነቢያት፡</persName>
               <persName xml:lang="gez" corresp="#n1" type="normalized">Ros Nabiyāt</persName>
               <persName xml:lang="gez" xml:id="n2" type="birth">ራስ፡ ባንየት፡</persName>
               <persName xml:lang="gez" corresp="#n2" type="normalized">Rās Bānyāt</persName>
                  
               <persName>
                  <roleName type="title">ʾazzāž , bāḥǝr Nagāš, bǝḥt waddad </roleName>
               </persName>
                  
                  <nationality type="Ethiopia"/>
                  <faith type="EOTC"/>
                  <occupation type="political">governor</occupation>
                 
               <floruit notBefore="1510" notAfter="1526">He was a prominent member of the ruling elite and nobility of the Ethiopian Empire on the eve of the Muslim invasion 
                  of <persName ref="PRS1500Ahmad">ʾAḥmad</persName>. He appears in the historiography of the sixteenth century with various titles. 
                  He is mentioned as <roleName type="title">ʾazzāž </roleName> and governor of <placeName ref="LOC5399Sabal">Šabal</placeName>, 
                  a small region in  <placeName ref="LOC3549Gojjam">Goǧǧām</placeName>,   in <date>1510</date>. He was appointed as 
                  <roleName type="title">bāḥǝr Nagāš </roleName> probably in <date>1524</date>, holding that office for two years. 
                  He appears as the only <roleName type="title">bǝḥt waddad</roleName> in the 18th year of the reign of <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>
                  <persName ref="PRS6229LebnaDe">Lǝbna Dǝngǝl</persName>,
                  in <date>1526</date>. During the Muslim war, <persName ref="PRS8212RosNabi">Ros Nābiyāt (Rās Bānyāt) </persName>
                     was the first  commander of the strategic province of <placeName ref="LOC2582Dawaro">Dawāro</placeName> where he was defeated. 
                     He also led several battles to defend the Christian kingdom from Muslims attacks.
                   
                  </floruit>
